This is my first attempt at a jQuery plugin. It is a simple carousel for images.

Simply create a structure like so...

<div>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <img>
    </li>
    <li>
      <img>
    </li>
   ....
  </ul>
</div>

and the plugin will do the rest.

OPTIONS

groupby: images to show at once
time: duration of animation

height: height of images
width: width of images
padding: space between images

loop: loop around when the edge is reached

title: title to add to the div

auto: auto-rotate the images
auto_inc: rate to auto-rotate in ms
mousestop: stop the carousel on mouseover

paginate: class on the page button div
listid: id on the div containing the list
activeid: id on the active button
next: id on 'next' button
prev: id on 'prev' button

nextimg: image for 'next' button
previmg: image for 'prev' button

